    <h2 id="why-nail-gummies">The Science Behind Nail Strength Supplements</h2>

    <p>Nails are composed primarily of keratin — a structural protein produced by specialized cells in the nail matrix (the tissue beneath the cuticle). The nail matrix requires specific nutrients to produce strong, durable keratin: biotin serves as a cofactor for keratin-producing enzymes, silica provides the mineral framework for keratin cross-linking, iron transports oxygen to the nail matrix cells, zinc supports cell division in the fast-growing nail bed, and vitamin C enables collagen synthesis in the nail bed tissue. When any of these nutrients is deficient, the nail matrix produces weaker keratin, resulting in brittle, splitting, peeling nails.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
      <span class="key-stat-num">25%</span>
      <p class="key-stat-txt">increase in nail thickness was observed in a clinical study published in the <em>Journal of the American Academy of Dermatology</em> after 6 months of 2,500mcg biotin supplementation. <strong>A separate study found that 63% of participants with brittle nails experienced reduced splitting and breakage</strong> with consistent biotin supplementation.</p>
    </div>

    <p>The critical factor in nail supplementation is patience. Fingernails grow approximately 3-4mm per month — it takes 4-6 months for a fully renewed nail to grow from the matrix to the fingertip. Toenails grow even slower at approximately 1mm per month, requiring 12-18 months for full renewal. Any nail supplement that promises "results in weeks" is misleading. The nutrients you take today support the nail cells being formed today — you will not see those stronger cells emerge as visible nail for months. Consistency over 3-6 months is the key to results.</p>

